<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910401-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>910401-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Hi-Shear Industries Inc.:   Defense Systems Corp. Unit   Is Closed Because of Losses</HL><DATE>04/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   HSI</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   Hi-Shear Industries Inc. said it closed Defense SystemsCorp., a Reno, Nev., subsidiary that makes aerospace defenseequipment.   Hi-Shear, North Hills, N.Y., said it closed the unitbecause of losses from two government contracts. In the yearended May 31, 1990, the pretax loss from Defense Systemstotaled $8.2 million. In the current fiscal year, the loss atthe end of February was $3.2 million.</LP><TEXT>   In a statement, Hi-Shear said Defense Systems was innegotiations with a &quot;government procuring agency&quot; aboutdisposition of two contracts. The company was to subcontractthe contracts in order to finish them, or negotiate an end tothe contracts with the procuring agency. The parent said ithad a $21.5 million investment in the unit.   Officials weren't available to comment on the company'sstatement.   Losses associated with the contracts, the companybelieves, were the result of defects in specificationsprovided by the procuring agency. Hi-Shear has received $11.1million so far for its work and holds a &quot;substantial amount&quot;of inventory.   Hi-Shear, a maker of aerospace fastening and electronicaircraft systems, said it is negotiating with severalpotential buyers for Defense Systems.</TEXT></DOC>